  "steps": [
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Identifying Cura\u00e7ao",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "centeredImage",
          "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/0_summary_curacao.png"
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/1920px-Curacao_in_its_region.svg.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/curacao/1920px-Curacao_in_its_region.svg.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Cura\u00e7ao is a constituent country in the Kingdom of the Netherlands located north of western Venezuela in the Caribbean Sea. As such, for country streaks purposes, it is counted as the Netherlands."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/image.png",
              "imageLink": "/images/curacao/image.png",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Cura\u00e7ao uses square licence plates that appear completely white through the blur.",
              "NOTE: While front plates are mandatory, a [minority](https://goo.gl/maps/rXKj6bBALkcMM5Cg9) will still not have front plates."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/image__284_29.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/o4zB8eW4K96Cd9bV9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "This **black car** with a **roof rack** is unique to Cura\u00e7ao."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/cw_cacti.webp",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/2WEdmyNf3ohqPYBJ9",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Due to Cura\u00e7ao\u2019s semi-arid climate, **cacti** can commonly be seen."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/image__281_29.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/vfu6drnkyNZH1ywMA",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Much of the architecture on Cura\u00e7ao consists of **simple, one storey bungalows** that are **pastel coloured**. Metal roofs are common on smaller shacks, while tiled roofs can be seen on more expensive houses. Additionally, multi storey villas can sometimes be seen."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/cw_signbackborder.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/1PqPxt6KXaVMtKyN7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "The coloured border or road signs can typically be seen continuing onto the back of the signs. These will generally be red or blue."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/cw_yellowsignpost.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/kpgkjQhcV36khysS6",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Blue street signs attached to the top of **yellow signposts** are common in Cura\u00e7ao."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/image__282_29.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/52UqrVVx2iqovBds7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "**White and black** striped traffic light posts can be seen in urban areas."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/image__283_29.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/CFpdApuPubbjrHWe7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.5
            },
            "text": [
              "Wooden poles with **three horizontal**, **alternating** insulators are common.",
              "NOTE: These poletops can also be found in Brazil, South Africa, and Eswatini."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "pole"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Regional  clues",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/rural.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/972dfR9bMJXSARF2A",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The western half of Cura\u00e7ao is characterised by a semi-arid **rural** **landscape** with green, but dry hills. Houses are spread apart, with the roads in the west quite narrow in width."
            ]
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "kind": "tip",
      "title": "Spotlight",
      "items": [
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/wind.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/j9NGzSbQVKaPbUo89",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "A line of **wind turbines** can be seen at this wind farm toward the southeast of Cura\u00e7ao. The coverage is also notably rainy."
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/bridge.png",
              "imageLink": "https://goo.gl/maps/5ZA2PefSwkeFfvFi7",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "The **Queen Juliana Bridge** is a wide four lane bridge in Willemstad. It can be recognised by the yellow and blue guardrails, and the view over the city."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "guardrail"
          ]
        },
        {
          "kind": "tip",
          "data": {
            "image": {
              "imageUrl": "/images/curacao/stick.png",
              "imageLink": "https://maps.app.goo.gl/ppUDmGzodvkND8588",
              "alt": "",
              "width": 0.573
            },
            "text": [
              "Grote Berg, located in the centre of the island, can be recognised by the **stick** stuck to the front of the camera lens."
            ]
          },
          "tags": [
            "coverage"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
